---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Terms of Use | Nubo Baby Tracker';
const description = 'Terms of Use for the Nubo Baby Tracker app and device. Learn about your rights, subscriptions, acceptable use, and how we protect your data.';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Terms of Use",
  "description": description,
  "url": "https://www.nubotracker.com/terms-of-use/",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Clicksie LLC",
    "url": "https://www.nubotracker.com"
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="overline">Legal</p>
        <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="page-hero-sub">
          These terms apply to the Nubo Baby Tracker app, device, and related services
          developed by Clicksie LLC.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-content">
      <div class="container policy-inner">
        <p class="policy-updated">Effective Jan 1, 2026</p>

        <div class="policy-summary">
          <p class="policy-notice">
            Nubo helps families track baby care routines. Nubo is not a medical device and is not
            intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any medical condition or illness.
          </p>
        </div>

        <article class="policy-body">

          <h2>1. Your Account and Use of Nubo</h2>
          <p>
            You can use core Nubo features without creating an account. Some features, including
            caregiver collaboration and backup and restore, may require sign-in through Apple,
            Google, or another supported provider. You agree to provide accurate information when
            you create or update a profile or account. You are responsible for keeping access to
            your device and account secure and for the activity that occurs through your account.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Baby Profiles, Logs, and Caregiver Sharing</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo lets you create baby profiles and log care events such as feeding, sleep, diapers,
            health notes, milestones, and reminders. If you invite caregivers, you choose to share
            the selected baby profile and related logs with those caregivers. Invited caregivers can
            view the shared baby profile and logs, create logs, and edit or delete logs. Only invite
            people you trust and remove access when it is no longer needed.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Subscriptions and Premium Features</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo may offer optional premium features. On iOS, Nubo may offer auto-renewable
            subscriptions through the Apple App Store. Subscription options shown in the app
            include the subscription title, duration, price, and any free trial terms available
            at the time of purchase.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Payment is charged to your Apple ID account at confirmation of purchase.</li>
            <li>Subscriptions automatically renew unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
            <li>Your account may be charged for renewal within 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
            <li>You can manage or cancel Apple subscriptions at <a href="https://apps.apple.com/account/subscriptions">Apple subscription settings</a>.</li>
            <li>If a free trial is offered and you purchase a subscription, any unused portion of the free trial may be forfeited where permitted by platform rules.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. App Store License Terms</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo is distributed through third-party app stores and platforms, including the Apple
            App Store and Google Play. Your use of Nubo may also be subject to the terms and
            policies of the platform where you downloaded the app.
          </p>
          <p>
            For the iOS app, Nubo uses Apple's standard Licensed Application End User License
            Agreement unless a separate custom EULA is provided in App Store Connect. You can
            review Apple's standard terms at
            <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/">Apple Standard EULA</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Device-Based and Promotional Premium Access</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo may grant premium access through an active subscription, a connected Nubo device,
            a promotional trial, or another eligibility rule described in the app. These access
            methods may have different durations and may change over time. If premium access ends,
            premium features may become unavailable unless you start or restore an eligible
            subscription.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>
            You agree not to misuse Nubo, interfere with its operation, attempt to access systems
            without permission, reverse engineer the app except where permitted by law, or use
            Nubo in a way that violates applicable law or the rights of others.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Voice and AI-Assisted Features</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo may include voice logging, text parsing, or AI-assisted features that help turn
            your input into structured baby care logs. These features are provided to make tracking
            easier, but you are responsible for reviewing entries for accuracy before relying on
            them or sharing them with caregivers.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Privacy and Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            Your use of Nubo is also governed by our
            <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>, which explains what information is
            stored on your device, what information may be processed when you use collaboration
            or backup features, and how to contact us with privacy questions.
          </p>
          <p>
            Nubo may rely on services from Apple, Google, Firebase, app stores, cloud providers,
            analytics providers, or other third parties. For example, Nubo may use platform
            sign-in services, encrypted cloud backup storage such as iCloud or Google Drive,
            Apple Push Notification Service and Firebase Cloud Messaging for push notifications,
            or diagnostics services that help us maintain app reliability. Those services are
            governed by their own terms and policies. We are not responsible for third-party
            services that we do not control.
          </p>

          <h2>9. No Medical Advice</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo is a tracking and organization tool. Nubo does not provide medical advice,
            diagnosis, treatment, or emergency services. Information in Nubo, including baby care
            logs, reminders, charts, notes, summaries, and AI-assisted outputs, is for
            informational purposes only and is not a substitute for advice from a qualified
            healthcare professional. Always contact a healthcare professional with questions about
            your baby's health or medical care.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Changes to Nubo or These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update Nubo, add or remove features, change premium offerings, or update these
            Terms of Use from time to time. If changes are material, we will take reasonable steps
            to notify you. Continued use of Nubo after changes become effective means you accept
            the updated terms.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Account Deletion and Termination</h2>
          <p>
            You may stop using Nubo at any time. You may delete baby profiles, logs, and
            account-related data through the app where those controls are available, or contact
            us for help. We may suspend or terminate access to Nubo if we believe these terms
            have been violated, if required by law, or if continued access would create risk for
            Nubo, other users, or our services.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Intellectual Property and User Content</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo, including its design, software, features, trademarks, and content, is owned by
            Clicksie LLC or its licensors and is protected by intellectual property laws. You may
            use Nubo only for your personal, non-commercial family care tracking.
          </p>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of the baby profile information, logs, notes, photos, and other
            content you enter into Nubo. You grant Clicksie LLC permission to store, process,
            display, transmit, and sync that content as needed to provide Nubo features such as
            local tracking, caregiver collaboration, backup and restore, notifications, and support.
          </p>

          <h2>13. Disclaimers and Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            Nubo is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. To the maximum extent
            permitted by law, Clicksie LLC disclaims warranties of merchantability, fitness for a
            particular purpose, and non-infringement. To the maximum extent permitted by law,
            Clicksie LLC is not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
            punitive damages arising from your use of Nubo.
          </p>

          <h2>14. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about these Terms of Use, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:support@clicksie.io">support@clicksie.io</a>.
          </p>

          <div class="policy-company">
            <p>
              Nubo Baby Activity Tracker<br />
              <strong>Clicksie LLC</strong><br />
              Copyright &copy; 2026 Clicksie LLC. All Rights Reserved.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>


<style>
  .policy-content {
    padding: 4rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .policy-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-updated {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: #999;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .policy-summary {
    background: var(--color-bg-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .policy-notice {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .policy-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .policy-body p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-body ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .policy-body ul li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #444;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .policy-body ul li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-brand);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.2em;
  }

  .policy-body a {
    color: var(--color-brand);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .policy-body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .policy-company {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border, #e5e5e5);
  }

  .policy-company p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 2;
  }
</style>
